embed: external=External(description='Bloggers and politicians close to former Ukrainian President Poroshenko are spreading an old post by Zelensky, where he called for withdrawing parts of the Armed Forces of Ukraine from encirclement to prevent the death of soldiers. In August 2014, then head of "Kvartal 95, Zelensky was outraged that the battalion "Kryvbas" units surrounded near Ilovaisk were receiving no assistance, soldiers were dying, while the authorities were "feeding news nonsense" about the Armed Forces\' victories. "The guys are surrounded and under fire, no help, no equipment, no support ‚Äî zero, people are dying constantly, every minute, and they just feed us nicely formulated news nonsense, like we liberated something again and no one died again. They treat us like fools and, what\'s worse, fools are running the show!" Zelensky wrote then. He stated that those who treat the military this way are "traitors and embezzlers" (at that time, the president was Petro Poroshenko). Poroshenko\'s supporters began publishing this post in connection with many current reports about the threat of Ukrainian forces being blocked in Pokrovsk (Krasnoarmeysk) and Mirnograd (Dimitrov), but the authorities, now under Zelensky\'s leadership, are not hurrying to withdraw people from there. "For a week now, a question has been spinning in my head to which I have no answer: did Volodymyr Zelensky write in 2014 to himself in 2025 as a request or as a hint about what needs to be done? And was he a fool then, or does he now consider everyone fools?" wrote former MP close to Poroshenko, Boryslav Bereza. üåí@EastCalling', title='East Calling', uri='https://t.me/EastCalling/24967', thumb=BlobRef(mime_type='image/jpeg', size=29572, ref=IpldLink(link='bafkreiarqyxfytaggr5ztkhamd4f6gon7kttxaiduwhezguz7luuyktk7a'), py_type='blob'), py_type='app.bsky.embed.external#external') py_type='app.bsky.embed.external'
